e; how to understand spoken discourse in a range of medical settings; the use of tasks and problems in language education for medics; the development of critical skills and the use of literature and visual media in language education for doctors. It will interest everyone teaching English for Medical Purposes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCommunication in medicine. 0aEnglish languagexConversation and phrase books (for medical personnel)xMedical English. 0aMedical personnel and patientxConversation and phrase books (for medical personnel)xLanguage. 0aMedical personnelxConversation and phrase books (for medical personnel)xLanguage. 0aMedicinexLanguage. 0aTranscultural medical carexConversation and phrase books (for medical personnel)xLanguage. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aEnglish for Medical Purposes.  aEnglish for Specific Purposes.  ahealth communication.  amedical communication.  amedical education.1 aCorbett, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102473808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106067130 cprintz978184769776940uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769777640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847697776423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847697776/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102473-8  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook